President Donald J. Trump has signed a proclamation declaring January 16 as National Religious Freedom Day in the United States. This day commemorates the anniversary of the 1786 Virginia Statute for Religious Freedom, which outlined the principles of freedom of religion. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of religious freedom and condemns extremism and violence against people of faith. It also highlights the Trump Administration's commitment to protecting religious freedom. The proclamation states that the free exercise of religion is a source of personal and national stability, and that faith brings life and hope to the world.